and ji (:0.01/d), figure 1 suggests that long-term cycles of approximatel
correct period are instead likely for tussock moth. Without assessing different methods of parameter estimation, the issue of whether the pathogen drives cycles in Douglas-fir tussock moth is clearly in doubt.
