the lifetime fecundity of female Oryctes as 90-150 eggs and the generation time as 20 wk. Zelazny and Alfiler (1986) give the proportion of Oryctes eggs surviving to adulthood as 0.03; these statistics result in a value of r = 0.002-0.006/d. Entwistle et al. (1983) give the lifetime fecundity of Gilpinia as 30-40 eggs. I was

