FIG. 5.-Plots of the wave speed, or the rate of advance of the disease, for the NPV of Orgyia as a function of each of the parameter values in eqq. (7)-(9). For the default parameter values, see figs. 3 and 4 with the addition of r = 0.005/d (Vezina and Peterman 1986). Wave speed versus (A) the transmission coefficient, v; (B) pathogen production rate, X; (C) carrying capacity, K; (D) pathogen decay rate, R; (E) disease-induced mortality rate, cx; (F) intrinsic rate of increase, r. As the graphs show, the model parameters vary enormously in the extent to which they affect the speed of the wave. In particular, the wave speed is very sensitive to small changes in the transmission coefficient v and the pathogen production rate X, which suggests that the rate of advance of the disease is quite sensitive to the infectiousness of the disease.
